data.title: Cliquepoint Data Foundation
data.meta_description: Cliquepoint Data Foundation was founded in 2010 to help Cleveland kids reduce negative online behaviors & to encourage responsible use of digital technology
data.text:
Cliquepoint Data Foundation was founded in 2010 with a mission to encourage the responsible use of digital technology and recently included the advocation of STEM for underrepresented groups

The Organization immediate focus however, is to rehabilitate and re-purposing the National Historic Register Eleanor B. Rainey Institute building, located at 1523 east 55th Street Cleveland, Ohio 44103.

The re-purpose building will be transform into a Nonprofit collaborative Co-working space, tentatively called the Cliquepoint Data Foundation: Settlement. The goal is to create a collaborative unified network of diverse Organizations under one roof with one goal, and that is to serve the collective needs of the Hough, Central, and Fairfax communities. Check back to this page periodically or send an email to contact@cliquepoint.org for updates on how your nonprofit Organization can be apart of the “Settlement Community Movement.”
